name: The Larkins
overview: Set in the late 1950â€™s, The Larkins follows the golden-hearted wheeler dealer Pop Larkin and his wife Ma, together with their six children, including the beautiful Mariette, as they bask in their idyllic and beautiful patch of paradise in Kent.

episodes.name: In Which We Meet the Larkin Family
episodes.overview: There is excitement at the approaching May Day Fair, but Mariette drops a bombshell and the tax man comes calling.

episodes.name: In Which the Larkins Woo Charley the Tax Man
episodes.overview: With their wit, charm and a little bit of cunning, the Larkins woo Charley the Tax Man. Mariette agrees to put her plans on hold and stay for the summer.

episodes.name: In Which Pop and Ma Go on holiday
episodes.overview: Ma is worried that Pop is working too hard and books a weekend in Margate, leaving Charley and Mariette to mind the kids. Margate, however, threatens to be a let-down.

episodes.name: In Which the Larkins Rescue The Railway Station
episodes.overview: News reaches Pop that the train station is to close. With the help of Miss Chand and the villagers, Pop seizes the opportunity to save the railway and make money along the way.

episodes.name: In Which Ma's Sister Bertha Comes To Visit
episodes.overview: The Larkins have visitors they would rather avoid. There is tension between Mariette and Charley, Alec Norman is up to his old dirty tricks and the truth about Tom Fisherâ€™s plans emerge. Can Primrose save the day, and where has Mariette disappeared to?

episodes.name: In Which the Larkins Are Determined to Convince Mariette to Stay
episodes.overview: The Larkins dash to the railway station and manage to stall Mariette's departure to France. They convince her to stay for a donkey derby/gymkhana and cocktail party in a few days.

episodes.name: The Larkins at Christmas
episodes.overview: Charley's parents come to visit the Larkins, but a quiet and respectful dinner plan goes awry when the village suffers a power cut.

episodes.name: Bad Neighbours
episodes.overview: Pop accepts a lucrative offer that he can't refuse, and the Larkins' new neighbours host a hilariously dire dinner party.

episodes.name: The Trap
episodes.overview: It's BBQ weather, and no-one throws a party like the Larkins - everyone is welcome, including the dubious Jerebohms, but a trap is set for Pop...

episodes.name: Love and Violence
episodes.overview: Ma issues Pop some tough love while playing Cupid between Primrose and the Reverend Candy, and an old friend of Pop's arrives in the village.

episodes.name: Wheels of Justice
episodes.overview: Ma and the children try to convince Pop to take the court case seriously, but he has fun on his mind and is conducting his own defence...

episodes.name: Pop in Prison
episodes.overview: The Larkins do all they can to get Pop out of prison - to keep his spirits up, Mariette tells him something that he is sworn to secrecy about...

episodes.name: Vengeance
episodes.overview: When Norma confesses to Ma that Pop was set up by the Jerebohms, Ma gets some help to organise her own sting operation... and get some revenge.
